      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRYX VIXEN (4) is back after a layoff of three months. Was very consistent last time in and closed the last prep in great style with a win at this circuit and distance. Readied with a nice trial so could prove hard to beat on her return. BETTORSWEETVICTORY (6) registered another strong performance last start when she battled on bravely for a 2.8m third at Cranbourne. That continued a run of top-four results. Another big run is on the cards. COLORADO GIRL (3) didn't do a bad job when fourth at Shepparton last time out. Draws lower and placed in her previous two outings. Go well. JILLIBY ILLUSION (9) was third from this row two back at Shepparton and has placed both times she has raced here.",
